reviews.review_text: Unfortunately.... This is some killer vintage DEAD, but the show sounds like crap.  Don't download, until you sample the tracks.

low sound this is not one to download, although is sbd?, the sound quality is very low, except dark star & hard to handle. the cryptical is filler on the 10th cosmic cuts about 56 sec. in. do the alligator>caution from the 12th. its well worth it.

tc plays bach! I personlly love this show. 69 was such a fukd year. the r&b and country tunes mixed with the lsd freak rock is just plain ridiculous.
check out the lite snippet of tc playing a js bach minuet btween mama tried and the yellow dog story (does that ever get old?) its amazing. 

ps: this is the worst quality sb i have ever heard, but it's still pretty good. i started my bootleg days with punk rock/ hardcore shows, so i have a wide berth.
Good Stuff From the point of view of somebody who loves the Dead, it is great to hear this show, go back in time and hear them play like they did in the early days.
Bookmark this! Very lovely, just right raw, like magic.
hot show great show, but hard to handle contains significant digital errors from a bad CD burn somewhere in the line
